  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world. It involves the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (such as funds from drug trafficking, corruption, or other criminal activities) appear legitimate by disguising their true origin. This practice undermines financial systems, facilitates crime, and damages economic integrity.\n\nCountries have enacted laws and regulations to combat money laundering, often in alignment with international standards set by organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF). Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including significant fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Therefore, it is considered a serious criminal offense.",
